"title": "5928: resentment, against God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5928",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Resentment against God or Jesus Christ is usually the consequence of a lack of faith or unbelief or as a response to adverse circumstances.</p>\n<h2>Israel's resentment against God expressed in constant grumbling</h2>\n<h3>Resentment at hardships and lack of provisions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:24\">EXO 15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:2-Exod16:3\">EXO 16:2–16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:3\">EXO 17:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:2-Num20:5\">NUM 20:2–20:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:4-Num21:5\">NUM 21:4–21:5</a></p>\n<h3>Resentment due to faithless fear</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:10-Exod14:11\">EXO 14:10–14:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:2-Num14:3\">NUM 14:2–14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:36\">NUM 14:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:27\">DEU 1:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:25\">PSA 106:25</a></p>\n<h2>God's response to Israel's resentment</h2>\n<h3>Punishment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:1\">NUM 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:27-Num14:30\">NUM 14:27–14:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:37\">NUM 14:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:26-Ps106:27\">PSA 106:26–106:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:10\">1CO 10:10</a></p>\n<h3>Merciful provision</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:4\">EXO 16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:8-Exod16:9\">EXO 16:8–16:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:11-Exod16:12\">EXO 16:11–16:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:5\">NUM 17:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:10\">NUM 17:10</a></p>\n<h2>Expressions of resentment</h2>\n<h3>At suffering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:1\">JOB 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:20-Job3:26\">JOB 3:20–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:11\">JOB 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:10\">1SA 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:1-Ps77:3\">PSA 77:1–77:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps142:2\">PSA 142:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:18\">JER 15:18</a></p>\n<h3>At apparently unjust treatment by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:20-Ruth1:21\">RUT 1:20–1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:2\">JOB 23:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:27\">ISA 40:27</a></p>\n<h3>At God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:18-Mark6:19\">MRK 6:18–6:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:42-1Kgs20:43\">1KI 20:42–20:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:4\">1KI 21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:10\">2CH 30:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:16</a></p>\n<h2>The folly of resentment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:2\">JOB 5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:21-Ps73:22\">PSA 73:21–73:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:12\">PRO 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:3\">PRO 19:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:39\">LAM 3:39</a></p>\n<h2>The evil of resentment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:13\">JOB 36:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:16\">JAS 3:14–3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:16\">JUD 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Resentment towards Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>At his miracles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:54-Matt13:58\">MAT 13:54–13:58</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:1-Mark6:6\">MRK 6:1–6:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:15\">MAT 21:15</a></p>\n<h3>At his teaching</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:12\">MAT 15:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:60-John6:61\">JHN 6:60–6:61</a></p>\n<h3>At his claims</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:41-John6:43\">JHN 6:41–6:43</a></p>",
